    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">i usually start off by bidding 3-5 because going first is kind of important.  say you win the bid you try to play as much stuff as you can then you exert Frodo to play your site 2,  there are no skirmish phase in that site, then you should have a hobbit stealth or something in your hand to deal with what you can at site three.<br />
<br />
With playing moria people tend to get through their deck somewhat fast which for this deck is a good thing.  you need to get the promises out as fast as you can.  vecause then sam with a hobbit sword is a standing 9, and frodo with sting is 10. <br />
<br />
the main thing for this deck is to not be afraid of what comes your way, bounder is amazing, and frodo and the party guest can heal them every turn so you can bounder almost everyturn.<br />
<br />
the shadow side is really easy to play, u just play what you need to do to stop them from keeping up with you for as long as you can. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
